JOHANNESBURG - Patrick Davidson will become the first South African pilot to compete in the Challenger Class of the Red Bull Air Race. The championship starts next year February in Abu Dhabi. It’s the premier air racing format in the world taking place in seven locations across Asia, Europe, and America. Davidson watched his grandfather and dad fly planes when he was growing up in Port Elizabeth. READ: Female ace takes on men in extreme-sport air racing He entered his first aerobatics competition at the age of twelve and 23 years later he has five SA titles and a World Championship title. Competing in the Red Bull Air Race is a step up, and a dream come true. Air-racing seems to a be a sport that a is split-second away from disaster due to the altitude and speed that the planes fly at. But Davidson states it’s a safe, controlled sport. eNCA